body:
I just copied the actual SQLite database file from Android and found that it only has one index. This could explain some of the performance issues.

Looking at the code (and docs), execSql executes a _single_ statement...and as a result seems to be only applying the first index.

I tested this by applying the following snippet at a convenient location:

```
        String[] indices = DATABASE_CREATE_INDICES.split(";");
        for (int i = 0; i < indices.length; i++) {
            mDb.execSQL(indices[i]);
        }
```

and found that much of the code ran faster.

I am not sure how best to get this into the next version...a DB upgrade maybe?

